In[38]:
def fill_price(row):
    '''      " " (price)     .
       ,   ,         , 
      ,     '''
    if pd.isna(row['price']):
        if row['middle_avg_bill'] > 0 and row['middle_avg_bill'] <= 375:
            return ''
        if row['middle_avg_bill'] > 375 and row['middle_avg_bill'] <= 750:
            return ''
        if row['middle_avg_bill'] > 750 and row['middle_avg_bill'] <= 1250:
            return ' '
        if row['middle_avg_bill'] >1250:
            return ''
    else:
        return row['price']

def hist_rating(df, column, groupby, title, xlabel, ylabel, binwidth, kde=False):
    '''          KDE.
    :
    df -     .
    column - str,  ,      .
    groupby - str,  ,      .
    binwidth - int,    .
    title - str,  .
    xlabel - str,    X.
    ylabel - str,    Y.
    kde -   KDE  
    '''
    #       'category'   
    for value in df[groupby].unique():
        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
        #      'category'
        food_places.loc[df[groupby] == value, column].plot(kind='hist',
                                                           density=True,
                                                           alpha=0.5,
                                                           bins=10,
                                                           label=f'{value}',
                                                           legend=True,
                                                           color='slategray'
                                                           )
        food_places.loc[df[groupby] == value, column].plot(
            kind='kde',
            label=f'KDE {value}')
        
        #             
        plt.title(f'{title} "{value}"')
        plt.xlabel(xlabel)
        plt.ylabel(ylabel)
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid()
        #plt.show()
    return
